TITLE: Creating a Basic CounterCubit in Dart
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a simple CounterCubit class that manages an integer state with increment functionality. Shows basic Cubit setup with initial state and state mutation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/felangel/bloc/blob/master/packages/bloc/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
/// A `CounterCubit` which manages an `int` as its state.
class CounterCubit extends Cubit<int> {
  /// The initial state of the `CounterCubit` is 0.
  CounterCubit() : super(0);

  /// When increment is called, the current state
  /// of the cubit is accessed via `state` and
  /// a new `state` is emitted via `emit`.
  void increment() => emit(state + 1);
}
```

