TITLE: Creating a Reactive Repository in Dart
DESCRIPTION: A repository that provides a Stream of data, allowing multiple blocs to listen to the same data source independently. This facilitates bloc communication through the domain layer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/felangel/bloc/blob/master/docs/src/content/docs/architecture.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
class AppIdeasRepository {
  Stream<AppIdea> getAppIdeas() async* {
    final ideas = [
      AppIdea("Delivery App", "An app for food delivery"),
      AppIdea("Doctor Appointment", "Book doctor appointments"),
      AppIdea("Learning Platform", "An app to learn programming")
    ];

    for (final idea in ideas) {
      yield idea;
      await Future.delayed(const Duration(seconds: 1));
    }

    // After we've gone through our ideas once,
    // start again from the beginning
    yield* getAppIdeas();
  }
}
```

