TITLE: Recommended State Naming Using Single Class in Dart
DESCRIPTION: Examples of proper state naming using a single class following the convention of 'BlocSubject + State' with a status enum (initial, success, failure, loading) to represent state changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/felangel/bloc/blob/master/docs/src/content/docs/naming-conventions.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
enum CounterStatus { initial, loading, success, failure }

class CounterState {
  const CounterState({
    this.status = CounterStatus.initial,
    this.count = 0,
    this.error,
  });

  final CounterStatus status;
  final int count;
  final Object? error;

  CounterState copyWith({
    CounterStatus? status,
    int? count,
    Object? Function()? error,
  }) {
    return CounterState(
      status: status ?? this.status,
      count: count ?? this.count,
      error: error != null ? error() : this.error,
    );
  }
}
```

