TITLE: Incorrect Bloc-to-Bloc Communication (Tight Coupling)
DESCRIPTION: An example of tight coupling between blocs that should be avoided. This creates a direct dependency between two blocs, making the code harder to maintain.
SOURCE: https://github.com/felangel/bloc/blob/master/docs/src/content/docs/architecture.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
class SecondBloc extends Bloc<SecondEvent, SecondState> {
  final FirstBloc firstBloc;
  late final StreamSubscription firstBlocSubscription;

  SecondBloc(this.firstBloc) : super(SecondState.initial()) {
    firstBlocSubscription = firstBloc.stream.listen((state) {
      // Do something with state of FirstBloc
      add(SecondEvent());
    });
  }

  @override
  Future<void> close() {
    firstBlocSubscription.cancel();
    return super.close();
  }
}
```

