TITLE: Using Builder with Multiple context.watch Calls in Flutter Bloc
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use Builder with multiple context.watch calls to create a MultiBlocBuilder effect. This pattern is useful when a widget depends on the state of multiple blocs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/felangel/bloc/blob/master/docs/src/content/docs/zh-cn/flutter-bloc-concepts.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
Builder(
  builder: (context) {
    final stateA = context.watch<BlocA>().state;
    final stateB = context.watch<BlocB>().state;
    final stateC = context.watch<BlocC>().state;

    //  BlocA BlocB,  BlocC  Widget
  }
);
```

